author: Gazette Staff
title: Strong first half lifts Rocky Mountain men to soccer win over Eastern Oregon
text:
Strong first half lifts Rocky Mountain men to soccer win over Eastern Oregon Gazette Staff 0 
The Rocky Mountain College men's soccer team used a barrage of goals in the first half to handily defeat Eastern Oregon Friday afternoon at Wendy's Field. 
Matthew Thomas, Jack Clancy, Tiago Ewald and Nolan Sherwood all scored first-half goals, helping the Battlin' Bears improve to 13-1 on the season. 
Steven Forbes assisted on two of the goals and Cole Catlin needed to make just one save to preserve the clean sheet. 
Rocky outshot EOU 11-1.
